    <p>LON­DON • Tot­ten­ham’s goal­keep­ing coach Nuno San­tos has been banned from the dugout for one game and fined £8,000 (S$14,078), after he ad­mit­ted to im­proper con­duct in Sunday’s 1-1 home Premier League draw with New­cas­tle, the Foot­ball As­so­ci­a­tion said yesterday.</p>
    <p>He was shown a red card fol­low­ing the fi­nal whis­tle for his protests after the video as­sis­tant ref­eree awarded a penalty to New­cas­tle in stop­page time for a con­tro­ver­sial hand­ball by Eric Dier.</p>


